    <h4>Description:</h4>
    <p>Vegetable Korma is a creamy, mildly spiced Indian curry made with a medley of fresh vegetables cooked in a rich coconut or cream-based sauce. It pairs wonderfully with naan or pulao.</p>

    <h4>Prep Time:</h4>
    <p>‚è±Ô∏è <strong>35 minutes</strong></p>

    <h4>Ingredients:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>1 cup mixed vegetables (carrots, peas, beans, potatoes)</li>
        <li>1 onion, finely chopped</li>
        <li>2 tomatoes, pureed</li>
        <li>1 tsp ginger-garlic paste</li>
        <li>1/4 cup yogurt or cream</li>
        <li>1/4 cup grated coconut or coconut milk (optional)</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp turmeric powder</li>
        <li>1 tsp coriander powder</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp garam masala</li>
        <li>1 tsp red chili powder</li>
        <li>2 tbsp oil</li>
        <li>Salt to taste</li>
        <li>Fresh coriander for garnish</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Instructions:</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>Boil the mixed vegetables until tender but not mushy. Drain and set aside.</li>
        <li>Heat oil in a pan. Add chopped onions and saut√© until golden brown.</li>
        <li>Add ginger-garlic paste and saut√© for a minute.</li>
        <li>Stir in tomato puree and cook until the oil separates.</li>
        <li>Add turmeric, chili, coriander powder, and salt. Cook for 2 minutes.</li>
        <li>Add yogurt/cream and coconut. Mix well and simmer for 3 minutes.</li>
        <li>Add the boiled vegetables and mix gently. Cook for 5‚Äì7 minutes.</li>
        <li>Sprinkle garam masala and garnish with chopped coriander.</li>
        <li>Serve hot with naan, paratha, or jeera rice.</li>
    </ol>
